The White House Office of the Press Secretary held a press briefing on April 11, 2013. Press Secretary Jay Carney answered questions from reporters on various topics including gun legislation, the budget, immigration, North Korea, Syria, drone strikes, and the President's meeting with CEOs from the banking industry. Carney also addressed concerns about the IRS, a German family seeking asylum, and demonstrations by minorities in Bangladesh and Sikhs in the US. He concluded by discussing the importance of engaging with business leaders and the President's commitment to reducing gun violence while protecting Second Amendment rights.